# Solicitation Review: FA940126Q0002 – Aircrew Facility Linens

---

## Solicitation Summary

### Key Dates
- **Posted:** November 7, 2025
- **Questions Due:** October 30, 2025 (5:00 PM MDT/MST)
- **Quotes Due:** November 14, 2025 (4:00 PM MDT/MST)
- **Quote Validity:** 90 days

---

### Location & Contacts
- **Place of Performance:** Building 917, Kirtland Air Force Base (KAFB), Albuquerque, NM 87117-0001
- **Contract Specialist:** Andrew Wiseman (andrew.wiseman.2@us.af.mil)
- **Contracting Officer:** Dakota Powell (dakota.powell@us.af.mil)
- **COR/POC:** Latesha Davis (latesha.davis@us.af.mil; 505-846-6298)

---

### Scope of Work
- **Services Required:** Management, supervision, personnel, supplies, transportation, equipment, and materials to provide laundry/dry cleaning for aircrew facility linens at KAFB.
- **Duties:** Pick-up/delivery, monthly invoicing with reporting, lost item tracking, and meeting federal/state/industry standards.
- **Hours:** Monday-Friday, excluding holidays.
- **Mission-Essential:** Must be able to continue services under crisis conditions.

---

### Submission Requirements
- **Format:** Email proposals in PDF, DOC, or XLS; max file size 30MB; no ZIP files.
- **Content:** Concise quotes (max 5-6 page technical plan), strictly adhering to the Statement of Work (PWS); no marketing/extraneous material. Clearly identify and justify exceptions if any.
- **Documentation:** Annex 1 Pricing, technical plan addressing Section 4.5 of PWS, company information (name, address, CAGE Code, POC).
- **Non-compliance:** May result in elimination from consideration.

---

### Evaluation Criteria
- **Best Value Based On:**
    - Technical (Acceptable/Unacceptable, must meet PWS requirements)
    - Price (all CLINs, options, and 6-month extension; must be fair/reasonable)
    - Award goes to lowest-priced technically acceptable proposal, evaluating in increments of four if necessary.

---

### Insurance & Regulatory
- **Insurance:** Not explicitly detailed; must comply with all applicable federal, state, and base safety/occupational standards.
- **Wage Compliance:** Adherence to Service Contract Labor Standards (see Wage Determination Attachment).
- **FOB Point:** Destination (KAFB)
- **Tax:** New Mexico Gross Receipts Tax may apply.

---

### Set Aside & Eligibility
- **Set Aside:** 100% SDVOSB (Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business)
- **NAICS:** 812320 (Drycleaning & Laundry Services except coin-operated); $8M size standard

---

### Documents Included
- Attachment 1: PWS – Aircrew Facility Linens
- Attachment 2: Wage Determination 2015-5443 Rev. 26 (08 July 2025)
- Attachment 3: SF1449 Solicitation FA940126Q0002 (provisions/clauses)
- Annex 1: Pricing Schedule

---

### Additional Context
- **No Incumbent:** New requirement.
- **Funding:** Award is contingent on future availability of funds; solicitation open to cancellation.
- **Monthly Reporting:** Mandatory on services, lost items, and charges.

---

## Qualifications Review

**Category: Government Contract – Laundry Services**

- **Scope & Fit:** In scope (facility laundry; no clinical care). Located in NM (acceptable). Mission-essential, with throughput reasonable for standard operations.
- **Eligibility:** Acceptable contract terms; SDVOSB set-aside fits our business structure.
- **Operational Capacity:** Volume and schedule within standard service capacity.
- **Timeline:** >2 weeks proposal window provided; meets timeline criteria.
- **Compliance & Risk:** No excessive bonding/insurance specified; routine regulatory compliance required.
- **Financial:** Not lowest-cost-only; fair/reasonable price, with structured evaluation. Project value not specified but duration (5 years + extension) and scope suggest meets contract ceiling preference.
- **Disqualifiers:** None surfaced based on provided information.

---

## Final Recommendation

**APPROVE** – Solicitation FA940126Q0002 fits our qualification criteria:
- The scope is within standard laundry services (no clinical/medical care needed).
- Location, eligibility (SDVOSB), timelines, and operational requirements are appropriate.
- No excessive compliance, risk, or financial disqualifiers identified.

---

**Action:**  
Prepare and submit a compliant technical and pricing proposal by November 14, 2025. Direct any clarifying questions to Andrew Wiseman or Dakota Powell before October 30, 2025.

